omeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>MATLAB</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://dgleich.github.io/matlab-bgl/\">MatlabBGL</a> - Graph library based on the C++ Boost Graph Library.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-23T13:09:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ike002jp/npartite\">npartite</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ike002jp/npartite\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">12</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":12,\"repo\":\"ike002jp/npartite\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Python algorithms for community detection in n-partite networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-23T13:09:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"TalAter/awesome-book-authoring","categoryHTML":"<h2>Must Reads</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.fasterj.com/articles/bookwriting.shtml\">Writing A Technical Book: Is It Worthwhile?</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-23T06:58:03.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"TalAter/awesome-book-authoring","categoryHTML":"<h2>Royalties, Advances, and Other Money Stuff</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.fasterj.com/articles/bookwriting.shtml\">Writing A Technical Book: Is It Worthwhile?</a> - The benefits for writing a technical book, and the basics of how book advances work.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-23T06:53:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"TalAter/awesome-book-authoring","categoryHTML":"<h2>Royalties, Advances, and Other Money Stuff</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.writersdigest.com/online-editor/how-book-advances-work-a-simple-explanation-for-writers\">How Book Advances Work – A Simple Explanation for Writers</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-23T06:53:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"TalAter/awesome-book-authoring","categoryHTML":"<h2>Royalties, Advances, and Other Money Stuff</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20130704110948/http://oreilly.com/oreilly/author/ch03.html#advance\">Typical O'Reilly Advance Structure</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-23T06:53:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"RomanTsegelskyi/rbooks","categoryHTML":"<h2>Advanced Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<h4>Data Manipulation with R, Second Edition <a href=\"https://www.packtpub.com/big-data-and-business-intelligence/data-manipulation-r-second-edition\">[Packt]</a></h4>\n<img src=\"http://ecx.images-amazon.com/images/I/51Jwp-z343L._SX403_BO1,204,203,200_.jpg\" width=\"200px\">\n<p>This book starts with the installation of R and how to go about using R and its libraries. We then discuss the mode of R objects and its classes and then highlight different R data types with their basic operations.</p>\n<p>The primary focus on group-wise data manipulation with the split-apply-combine strategy has been explained with specific examples. The book also contains coverage of some specific libraries such as lubridate, reshape2, plyr, dplyr, stringr, and sqldf. You will not only learn about group-wise data manipulation, but also learn how to efficiently handle date, string, and factor variables along with different layouts of datasets using the reshape2 package.</p>\n<p>By the end of this book, you will have learned about text manipulation using stringr, how to extract data from twitter using twitteR library, how to clean raw data, and how to structure your raw data for data mining.</p>","updatedAt":"2016-04-23T02:14:07.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"qinwf/awesome-R","categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Interpreters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.kent.ac.uk/projects/cxxr/\">CXXR</a> - Refactorising R into C++.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-23T01:05:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"qinwf/awesome-R","categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Interpreters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.pqr-project.org/\">pqR</a> - a \"pretty quick\" implementation of R</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-23T01:05:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"qinwf/awesome-R","categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Interpreters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.renjin.org/\">renjin</a> - a JVM-based interpreter for R.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-23T01:05:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"qinwf/awesome-R","categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Interpreters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rho-devel/rho\">rho</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/rho-devel/rho\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">131</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":131,\"repo\":\"rho-devel/rho\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Refactor the interpreter of the R language into a fully-compatible, efficient, VM for R.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-23T01:05:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"qinwf/awesome-R","categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Interpreters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://spotfire.tibco.com/discover-spotfire/what-does-spotfire-do/predictive-analytics/tibco-enterprise-runtime-for-r-terr\">TERR</a> - TIBCO Enterprise Runtime for R.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-04-23T01:05:10.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1461369600000,"to":1461